{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, you--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I just want to tell you that being locked up in a little apartment for eight months-- I think I was out maybe three or four times.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the evening, the boys would take me out for an airing a couple-- a few times. 'Tedious' is the word.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The stress is much less, and the boredom is much more.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So-- but that this is, again, a sort of a-- a quiet interval.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, when my father came-- he had survived the first attack and the first uprising of the ghetto of Warsaw and came out after the first uprising.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So when he came, he told us about it and how terrible it was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was an underground paper that the young men would bring.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Both of them were involved with the underground, as were most young-- young men in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they knew [? when ?] the ghetto was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They told us about it, but they didn't tell us the details, out of pity for us or compassion.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At the end of the eight months we were running out of money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And obviously, they could not support us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We didn't pay them an exorbitant amount, but we had to support ourselves.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had to pay them rent.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We heard, via the-- the grapevine, through their nephew, the young-- the man that my father had contacted, that a very peculiar thing was happening in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There was no ghetto of Warsaw anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were no official Jews alive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But all of a sudden, the Germans were negotiating through Switzerland, with-- with the Swiss, for some trucks and other supplies that they by then needed rather badly.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This was in the spring of 1943.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
